{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06561ee3ca0956a45a4b69b0a8ce650a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n## Trust States\n\n| State | Meaning | When it occurs |\n|---|---|---|\n| `static_verified` | All facts passed static verification only | `verification_mode = \"static\"`, 0 rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:131`) |\n| `llm_verified` | All facts passed LLM verification (promoted from static) | `verification_mode = \"llm\"`, 0 total rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:221`) |\n| `partial_llm` | LLM verification ran; some facts rejected | `verification_mode = \"llm\"`, ≥1 rejected fact → `omitted_facts > 0` (`src/cluster.ts:221`, `src/clusterRefresh.ts:179`) |\n\n## What differentiates full vs partial: `omitted_facts`\n\n`src/clusterRefresh.ts:176-182`:\n\n```ts\nconst omittedFacts = typeof content.omitted_facts === \"number\" ? content.omitted_facts : 0;\nif (status === \"llm_verified\") {\n  return omittedFacts > 0 ? \"partial_llm\" : \"llm_verified\";\n}\nreturn omittedFacts > 0 ? \"partial_static\" : \"static_verified\";\n```\n\n`omitted_facts` accumulates from both the static verifier (rejected count) and the LLM verifier (additional rejected count) at `src/cluster.ts:220`.\n\n## Consult gating\n\n`cluster_consult` (`src/clusterConsult.ts:55`) only proceeds if:\n- `factsheet.status === \"llm_verified\"`, **or**\n- `cluster.static_factsheet_policy === \"allow\"` (allows `static_verified` too)\n\nSo `partial_llm` is consult-blocked — it exists as an audit artifact but cannot serve `cluster_consult` calls without operator intervention."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":134302,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1bc568d1-5a5f-4314-b4be-00aca006f5e1","uuid":"810d4e1a-a645-4377-a44c-b1fd7b5b198f"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":25675,"duration_api_ms":25627,"num_turns":1,"result":"\n\n## Trust States\n\n| State | Meaning | When it occurs |\n|---|---|---|\n| `static_verified` | All facts passed static verification only | `verification_mode = \"static\"`, 0 rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:131`) |\n| `llm_verified` | All facts passed LLM verification (promoted from static) | `verification_mode = \"llm\"`, 0 total rejected facts (`src/cluster.ts:221`) |\n| `partial_llm` | LLM verification ran; some facts rejected | `verification_mode = \"llm\"`, ≥1 rejected fact → `omitted_facts > 0` (`src/cluster.ts:221`, `src/clusterRefresh.ts:179`) |\n\n## What differentiates full vs partial: `omitted_facts`\n\n`src/clusterRefresh.ts:176-182`:\n\n```ts\nconst omittedFacts = typeof content.omitted_facts === \"number\" ? content.omitted_facts : 0;\nif (status === \"llm_verified\") {\n  return omittedFacts > 0 ? \"partial_llm\" : \"llm_verified\";\n}\nreturn omittedFacts > 0 ? \"partial_static\" : \"static_verified\";\n```\n\n`omitted_facts` accumulates from both the static verifier (rejected count) and the LLM verifier (additional rejected count) at `src/cluster.ts:220`.\n\n## Consult gating\n\n`cluster_consult` (`src/clusterConsult.ts:55`) only proceeds if:\n- `factsheet.status === \"llm_verified\"`, **or**\n- `cluster.static_factsheet_policy === \"allow\"` (allows `static_verified` too)\n\nSo `partial_llm` is consult-blocked — it exists as an audit artifact but cannot serve `cluster_consult` calls without operator intervention.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"1bc568d1-5a5f-4314-b4be-00aca006f5e1","total_cost_usd":0.093572,"usage":{"input_tokens":3138,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":131264,"output_tokens":490,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations